"[{'role': 'user', 'content': 'My Photoshop application is crashing every time I try to save a file.'}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "I'm sorry to hear that you're having trouble with Photoshop. To better assist you, could you please tell me which version of the application you're using?"}
 {'role': 'user', 'content': "I'm using Photoshop CC 2020."}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Thank you. Before the crash occurred, were there any specific steps you took or error messages you received?'}
 {'role': 'user', 'content': "I didn't get any error messages. I just clicked 'Save' and the application crashed."}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "I see. Let's try a few troubleshooting steps. First, please ensure that your system meets the minimum requirements for Photoshop CC 2020. You can find this information on Adobe's website."}
 {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Yes, my system meets the requirements.'}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "Alright. Next, please try resetting your Photoshop preferences. To do this, press and hold Ctrl + Alt + Shift (Windows) or Cmd + Opt + Shift (Mac) while launching Photoshop. When prompted, click 'Yes' to delete the settings file."}
 {'role': 'user', 'content': 'I did that, but the problem still persists.'}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "I'm sorry to hear that. In this case, it might be helpful to repair your Photoshop installation. To do this, open the Creative Cloud desktop application, click on the gear icon, and select 'Preference.' Then, click 'Creative Cloud' and choose 'Apps.' Finally, find Photoshop CC 2020, click the three dots, and select 'Repair Install.'"}
 {'role': 'user', 'content': "I don't see the 'Repair Install' option."}
 {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "In that case, I would recommend contacting Adobe's support team for further assistance. You can find their contact information on Adobe's website. They have the tools and resources to help you resolve this issue."}]"

